all the wild horses we know.

00:20:02.279 --> 00:20:07.317 position:7% line:83% align:start
And we would swim and we would
ride into the woods and...

00:20:07.350 --> 00:20:09.986 position:10% line:89% align:start
Oh well, you know, don't you?

00:20:12.189 --> 00:20:14.692 position:24% line:83% align:start
- That would be the
greatest summer banquet.

00:20:14.725 --> 00:20:17.260 position:7% line:89% align:start
Only my sister could create it.

00:20:36.380 --> 00:20:39.115 position:27% line:89% align:start
(fire crackling)

00:20:42.587 --> 00:20:45.723 position:21% line:83% align:start
- [Narrator] The air
grew crisp, cooler.

00:20:50.495 --> 00:20:53.030 position:7% line:89% align:start
But they said nothing about it.

00:20:53.064 --> 00:20:56.167 position:21% line:89% align:start
(peaceful harp music)

00:21:17.823 --> 00:21:20.258 position:33% line:89% align:start
(quiet gasp)

00:21:26.565 --> 00:21:27.399 position:38% line:89% align:start
- Ronja!

00:21:30.134 --> 00:21:31.168 position:30% line:89% align:start
- What's wrong?

00:21:33.639 --> 00:21:37.108 position:10% line:89% align:start
You're not afraid of the fog?

00:21:37.141 --> 00:21:41.045 position:13% line:83% align:start
Do you think that after all
this time we'll get lost?

00:21:42.381 --> 00:21:46.552 position:30% line:83% align:start
(girls singing)
(quiet gasp)

00:21:52.591 --> 00:21:53.792 position:33% line:89% align:start
Do you hear?

00:21:53.825 --> 00:21:58.163 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's them, it's the unearthly
ones with their siren song.

00:21:58.196 --> 00:22:01.266 position:24% line:83% align:start
Oh, at last, I can
hear them for myself.

00:22:02.768 --> 00:22:06.806 position:16% line:83% align:start
- But, don't you remember
hearing that song before?

00:22:06.839 --> 00:22:09.575 position:13% line:89% align:start
- No, I've never heard it.

00:22:09.608 --> 00:22:12.611 position:21% line:83% align:start
They sing their evil
songs to try and lure us

00:22:12.645 --> 00:22:14.513 position:19% line:89% align:start
down to the underworld.

00:22:14.546 --> 00:22:15.314 position:38% line:89% align:start
They do.

00:22:16.315 --> 00:22:17.416 position:30% line:89% align:start
- Yes, they do.

00:22:18.818 --> 00:22:23.155 position:13% line:83% align:start
Ronja, please don't tell me
you'd like to follow them.

00:22:23.188 --> 00:22:26.224 position:35% line:89% align:start
(laughing)

00:22:26.258 --> 00:22:29.362 position:27% line:83% align:start
- You're mad, why
would anyone do that?

00:22:29.395 --> 00:22:32.097 position:7% line:89% align:start
Because Noddle-Pete, he said...

00:22:35.868 --> 00:22:37.637 position:24% line:89% align:start
- Noddle-Pete what?

00:22:37.670 --> 00:22:39.137 position:27% line:89% align:start
What did he say?

00:22:42.175 --> 00:22:44.277 position:21% line:89% align:start
- It doesn't matter.

00:22:44.310 --> 00:22:47.113 position:30% line:89% align:start
(girls singing)

00:22:53.720 --> 00:22:58.892 position:16% line:83% align:start
- When the unearthly ones
come into the forest and sing,

00:22:58.926 --> 00:23:01.461 position:19% line:89% align:start
you know it is autumn.

00:23:02.729 --> 00:23:04.898 position:35% line:89% align:start
(laughing)

00:23:07.567 --> 00:23:13.841 position:16% line:83% align:start
And then, soon, winter'll
come rushing over.

00:23:13.874 --> 00:23:17.911 position:27% line:89% align:start
Oh dear me, yes.

00:23:22.315 --> 00:23:26.487 position:16% line:83% align:start
- [Narrator] Next time on
Ronja, the Robber's Daughter.

